 (167,'IDS 251','Nature, Technology and Humanity','A thematic look at the relationship among nature, technology and our everyday lives.  Topics explored include contemporary health and environmental issues from a personal, local and global viewpoint.  Emphasis is on critical analysis of information and application of knowledge to solutions for real world problems. In addition, we hope improve the ways in which you gather information and critically evaluate information. This section of NTH has the overarching theme of sustainability because it offers a chance for immediate, everyday application of the information we are studying.  It is my intent to allow you to explore not only the environmental issues we have selected, but to enable you opportunities to learn about ideas that catch your own interest as well.  You will study the theme through many genres, including essays from popular magazines, books, films, and discussions as well is in your own writing.  In groups and individually, you will research outside sources—written, visual, and human—and we will become our own sources on these issues, too.',3.0,NULL,1,NULL),
 (168,'IDS 499','Seminar','The objective of seminar is to help students successfully navigate their college experience, understand and build connections to supportive and professional communities and to prepare for their future careers. Through seminar, students will develop skills and abilities necessary for success in college and beyond. Seminar is an important mechanism for personal growth and development and an essential point of connection for students and faculty mentors and as such seminar is required by all students in his or her declared major each semester.',3.0,NULL,1,NULL),
 (169,'IRM 221','Principles of Insurance & Risk Management','An introduction to the concept of risk, the process of risk management, and the field of insurance, including fundamental doctrines, historical background, social value, economic influence, loss exposures and protection, insurance regulation, insurance carriers, reinsurance, marketing, underwriting and claims adjusting. This course includes examination of the Michigan Essential Insurance Act and how this law addresses the social responsibility of the insurance business and its attempt to address social injustice. This course will also help students prepare for the INS 21 national examination administered by the Insurance Institute of America.',3.0,NULL,1,NULL),
